																								 Mumbai, Dec. 21: Finance minister P. Chidambaram today suggested that there may be a moderation of taxes in the forthcoming union budget. We believe taxes must be moderate and must be administered in a taxpayer-friendly manner, he said. I am happy with the tax compliance. In the three-and- a-half years of the UPA government, tax compliance improved dramatically, partly because of greater respect for tax payers, he added.
																								 Mumbai, Dec. 21: The finance ministry today said the local subsidiary of a foreign company is liable to pay fringe benefit tax (FBT) on shares allotted to Indian employees. Even if such securities are allotted by foreign holding companies to Indian employees outside the country, they come under FBT purview. 
																								 New Delhi, Dec. 21: Idea Cellular and Spice Telecom today dared the government to allocate spectrum to operators who submitted applications after them. We caution the DoT that no GSM initial spectrum allocation pertaining to application subsequent to ours for nine service areas can be entertained, Idea Cellular said in a letter.
																								 Coimbatore, Dec. 21: India today expressed confidence that work on the proposed $7-billion Iran-Pakistan -India gas pipeline project will start by March next year. India hopes to finalise a transit fee agreement with Islamabad before that.
																								 Calcutta, Dec. 21: The stock, money and commodity markets were closed today on account of Eid-ul-zuha.

